### INTENT ###
Add deterministic completeness checks to the governed rule-registry migration map. Keep this slice separate from coverage expansion, release work, GUI work, and documentation migration.

### NEW MIGRATION MAP FIELD ###
- known_legacy_rule_ids lists every known legacy rule id expected to have an explicit disposition.

### NEW VALIDATOR RULES ###
- known_legacy_rule_ids must be non-empty.
- every known legacy rule id must have a migration entry.
- every migration entry must be included in known_legacy_rule_ids.
- migration status must be one of: migrated, archived, rejected.
- migrated entries must reference an active mechanism.
- terminal archived/rejected entries must not set replaced_by.
- migration_reason and evidence checks remain active.

### TEST COVERAGE ###
- current repository state validates.
- CLI still passes current repository state.
- missing known_legacy_rule_ids is rejected.
- missing migration for known legacy rule is rejected.
- unindexed migration entry is rejected.
- invalid migration status is rejected.
- archived terminal status is accepted.
- terminal status with replaced_by is rejected.

### OUT OF SCOPE ###
- no coverage expansion
- no release, tag, DOI, or GUI work
- no broad documentation migration

### GATE EXPECTATION ###
CI must validate before merge. Relevant expectations:
- test_rule_registry_validator
- workflow-guard
- patch-preflight
